PRETORIA, February 11  – The National Education, Health and Allied Workers Union (Nehawu) on Monday announced a national strike set to affect “all the technical and vocational education and training (TVET) and community education and training (CET) colleges” across South Africa. “The strike will commence at workplaces on the 14th of February in the morning and run indefinitely until all our demands are met by the department of higher education and training (DHET),” Nehawu general secretary Zola Saphetha spoke to journalists in Pretoria. (ANA)